<subsection xml:id="subsec-addition-of-integers">
    <title>Addition of integers on a Number Line</title>
    <activity>
            <p>
                <alert>Work in groups</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="1. ">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Draw a number line similar to the one shown below.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="addition-of-integers-1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[thick,&lt; - &gt;](-6.5,0) -- (6.5,0);
                                    \foreach \x in {1,...,6} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {-1,-2,-3,-4,-5,-6} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Starting at <m>(+1)</m> on the number line, move <m>3</m> steps to the right and circle the number at the end of the <m>3rd</m> step.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Starting at <m>(-5)</m> on the number line, move <m>7</m> steps to the right and circle the number at the end of the <m>7th</m> step.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            What operation do you notice in step <m>2</m> and in step <m>3</m>?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Discuss and share your findings with the rest of the class.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
    </activity>
    <p><m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m></p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Consider <m>(+2) + (+3)</m>: when adding <m>(+3)</m>, a <alert>positive integer</alert>, to <m>(+2)</m>, 
                    we start at <m>(+2)</m> on the number line and move <m>3</m> steps to the <alert>right</alert>.
                </p>
                <image>
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="addition-of-integers-2">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-3.5,0) -- (7.5,0);
                        
                            \foreach \x in {-3,...,-1} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                            }
                        
                            \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                            \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                        
                            \foreach \x in {1,...,7} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                            }
                            % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (2,0.1) to[bend left=60] (3,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (3,0.2) to[bend left=60] (4,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (4,0.2) to[bend left=60] (5,0.1);
                            
                            % Start label
                            \draw[] (2,0) -- (2,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (2,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                            
                            % Stop label
                            \draw[] (5,0) -- (5,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (5,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};
                            
                            \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (2,0) circle(0.1);
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Consider <m>(+1) + (-5)</m>: when adding <m>(-5)</m>, a <alert>negative integer</alert>, to <m>(+1)</m>, 
                    we start at <m>(+1)</m> on the number line and move <m>5</m> steps to the <alert>left</alert>.
                </p>
                <image>
                    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                    <latex-image label="addition-of-integers-3">
                        \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-5.5,0) -- (5.5,0);
                            
                            \foreach \x in {-5,...,-1} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                            }
                            
                            \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                            \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 
                            
                            \foreach \x in {1,...,5} {
                                \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                            }
                            % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                            \draw[red,-&gt;] (1,0.1) to[bend right=60] (0,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (0,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-1,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (-1,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-2,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (-2,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-3,0.1);
                            \draw[red,- &gt;] (-3,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-4,0.1);
                            
                            % Start label
                            \draw[] (1,0) -- (1,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (1,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                            
                            % Stop label
                            \draw[] (-4,0) -- (-4,0.5);
                            \node[above] at (-4,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};
                            
                            \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (1,0) circle(0.1);
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                    </latex-image>
                </image>
            </li>
        </ul>        
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Use a number line to work out the following:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(-8) + (+3)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(+1) + (-4)</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
               <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(-8) + (+3)</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Draw the number line as shown below.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers1-part1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-8.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-8,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,...,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                            Locate the <m>(-8)</m> on the number line.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers1-part2">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-8.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-8,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,...,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }
                                    \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (-8,0) circle(0.1);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                             From the <m>(-8)</m>, move <m>3</m> spteps to the right, because the second
                             number <m>(+3)</m> is positive. 
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers1-part3">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-8.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-8,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,...,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }
                                    % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (-8,0.1) to[bend left=60] (-7,0.1);
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (-7,0.2) to[bend left=60] (-6,0.1);
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (-6,0.2) to[bend left=60] (-5,0.1);
                                    
                                    % Start label
                                    \draw[] (-8,0) -- (-8,0.5);
                                    \node[above] at (-8,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                                    
                                    % Stop label
                                    \draw[] (-5,0) -- (-5,0.5);
                                    \node[above] at (-5,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};
                                    
                                    \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (-8,0) circle(0.1);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                (-8) + (+3) = (-5)
                            </me>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(+1) + (-4)</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Draw the number line as shown below.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers2-part1">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-5.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-5,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,2,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                            Locate the <m>(+1)</m> on the number line.
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers2-part2">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-5.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-5,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,2,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }
                                    \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (1,0) circle(0.1);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                             From the <m>(+1)</m>, move <m>4</m> spteps to the right, because the second
                             number <m>(-4)</m> is negative. 
                        </p>
                        <image>
                            <shortdescription></shortdescription>
                            <latex-image label="number-line-addition-of-integers2-part3">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[&lt; - &gt;](-5.5,0) -- (3.5,0);

                                    \foreach \x in {-5,...,-1} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {-\x}; 
                                    }

                                    \draw (0,0.1) -- (0,-0.1);
                                    \node[below] at (0,-0.1) {0}; 

                                    \foreach \x in {1,2,3} {
                                        \draw (\x,0.1) -- (\x,-0.1); 
                                        \node[below] at (\x,-0.1) {+\x}; 
                                    }

                                    % Draw curved arrows for jumps
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (1,0.1) to[bend right=60] (0,0.1);
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (0,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-1,0.1);
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (-1,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-2,0.1);
                                    \draw[red,- &gt;] (-2,0.2) to[bend right=60] (-3,0.1);
                                    
                                    % Start label
                                    \draw[] (1,0) -- (1,0.5);
                                    \node[above] at (1,0.55) {\textbf{start}};
                                    
                                    % Stop label
                                    \draw[] (-3,0) -- (-3,0.5);
                                    \node[above] at (-3,0.55) {\textbf{stop}};

                                    \draw[thick,fill=red,red] (1,0) circle(0.1);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                (+1) + (-4) = (-3)
                            </me>
                        </p>
                    </li>
               </ol> 
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
</subsection>